        <ol class="london-core">
          <li><strong>Lovebites at O2 Academy Islington</strong> (Mon — the anchor, non-negotiable).</li>
          <li><strong>Broken By The Scream at The Dome, Tufnell Park</strong> (Sun — J-metal on your free night, the find of the trip).</li>
          <li><strong>Cart and Horses, Stratford</strong> — Iron Maiden ground zero, the one landmark worth crossing town for.</li>
          <li><strong>Raven Records, Camden</strong> — records + metal coffee + the world’s only alcohol-free metal bar.</li>
        </ol>
        <p class="london-prose">
          Everything else — All Ages, Denmark Street, Sister Ray, the Black Heart, the
          Marquee plaque — is gravy.
        </p>
      </section>

