        <h2 class="london-day__title">Tuesday, August 4 <span class="london-day__sub">— Getting to Heathrow</span></h2>
        <div class="london-prose">
          <p>
            Noon international flight. Be at the airport by ~9:30–10:00AM. Recommended
            departure from Islington: leave the hotel by ~8:00–8:15AM.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Tube only:</strong> Northern line (Angel) → King’s Cross, then Piccadilly line direct to Heathrow. Cheapest, ~75–90 min, no changes after King’s Cross. Leave by ~8:00AM.</li>
            <li><strong>Faster:</strong> Northern → King’s Cross, Elizabeth line → Paddington, then Heathrow Express (15 min). Pricier but quickest; leave by ~8:30AM.</li>
            <li><strong>Taxi / ride-share:</strong> ~45–70 min depending on traffic; build in extra for a Tuesday morning. Leave by ~8:15–8:30AM.</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>Bottom line:</strong> out the door by 8:15AM at the latest. No touring — this is a travel morning.</p>
        </div>
